Class HaVmOverrides

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.vmware.appliance.vcenter.settings.v1.config.components.inventory.cluster.ha.HaVmOverrides

    StaticStructure, Structure, java.io.Serializable

    public final class HaVmOverrides
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, StaticStructure
    The VmOverrides data object contains the HA configuration settings for vm as a override from cluster. All fields are optional.

      • getVmRestartPriorityTimeout

        public java.lang.Long getVmRestartPriorityTimeout()
        This setting is used to specify a maximum time the lower priority VMs should wait for the higher priority VMs to be ready. If the higher priority Vms are not ready by this time, then the lower priority VMs are restarted irrespective of the VM ready state. This timeout can be used to prevent the failover of lower priority VMs to be stuck infinitely. If null or empty, the value is skipped.
        Returns:
        The current value of the property.

If the higher priority Vms are not ready by this time, then the lower priority VMs are restarted irrespective of the VM ready state. This timeout can be used to prevent the failover of lower priority VMs to be stuck infinitely. If null or empty, the value is skipped.
